review_blob: Flavoursome - powerfully citrussy and fruitty. Smooth, very much a red wine beer - best drunk with food as a compliment.
Typically CUB - Clean crisp and bitter. Best drunk in large quantities. Easier on the palette than most of its brewery bedfellows. Great price!
Its not a fancy pants beer - with strong textures and flavours. Its a beer for drinkers, clean crisp taste, bitter. Great for whittling away a thirst.
Well presented Carlton beer, low on flavour, quite watery. Moderate to strong bitter taste.
You can go past a coopers on tap! Mirky cloudy beer. Fruity almost foresty flavour. Some bitterness.
